{"title_page": "Gerhard Potma", "text_new": "{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Gerhard Potma\n| image          = Gerhard-potma.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = Gerhard Potma in May 2005\n| birth_name     =\n| fullname       = Gerhardus Johannes Cornelis Potma\n| nickname       =\n| nationality    = Dutch\n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1967|08|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Sneek]]\n| death_date     = {{Death date and age|2006|03|31|1967|08|29|df=y}}\n| death_place    =\n| height         = {{convert|1.84|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         =\n| classes        = [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]]<br />[[Soling]]\n| club           =\n| collegeteam    =\n| coach          =\n| medaltemplates-title = Competition record\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCountry|{{NED}}}}\n {{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]] [[File:Olympic rings without rims.svg|50px]]}}\n  {{Medal|18th|[[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]]|[[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]]}}\n  {{Medal|15th|[[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|1996 Savannah]]|[[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|Soling]]}}\n| show-medals    = yes\n| updated        = 20 February 2014\n}}\n\n'''Gerhard Potma''' (29 August 1967, in [[Sneek]] \u2013 31 March 2006, in Sneek) was a [[sailor]] from the [[Netherlands]],<ref name=\"A\" /> who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]]. Potma as crew in the Dutch  [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]]<ref name=\"B\" /> with his brother, [[Willem Potma]],<ref name=\"C\" /> as helmsman took the 18th place.<ref name=\"D\" /><ref name=\"E\" /> In [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|1996]] Potma returned to the Olympics in [[Savannah, Georgia|Savannah]]. Again with his brother as helmsman and [[Frank Hettinga]] as crew. Potma took 15th place in the [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|Soling]].<ref name=\"A\" />\n{{Footer Dutch Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{1992DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n{{1996DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n==Further reading==\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Olympics (Barcelona)]] {{flagteam|ESP|1992 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n   |url        = http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1992/1992s1.pdf\n   |title      = Official Report of the Games of the XXV Olympiad Barcelona 1992, Volume I The Challenge: From the idea to the nomination\n   |publisher  = COOB'92 S.A.\n   |location   = Barcelona\n   |year       = 1992\n   |format     = PDF\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}\n* {{cite web\n   |url        = http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1992/1992s2.pdf\n   |title      = Official Report of the Games of the XXV Olympiad Barcelona 1992, Volume II The Means: Objectives, resources and venues\n   |publisher  = COOB'92 S.A.\n   |location   = Barcelona\n   |year       = 1992\n   |format     = PDF\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}\n* {{cite web\n   |url        = http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1992/1992s3.pdf\n   |title      = Official Report of the Games of the XXV Olympiad Barcelona 1992, Volume III The Organisation: The preparation of the Games\n   |publisher  = COOB'92 S.A.\n   |location   = Barcelona\n   |year       = 1992\n   |format     = PDF\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}\n* {{cite web\n   |url        = http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1992/1992s4.pdf\n   |title      = Official Report of the Games of the XXV Olympiad Barcelona 1992, Volume IV The Games: Sixteen days in summer\n   |location   = Barcelona\n   |year       = 1992\n   |format     = PDF\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}\n* {{cite web\n   |url        = http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1992/1992s5.pdf\n   |title      = Official Report of the Games of the XXV Olympiad Barcelona 1992, Volume V The Results\n   |publisher  = COOB'92 S.A.\n   |location   = Barcelona\n   |year       = 1992\n   |format     = PDF\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|1996 Olympics (Savannah)]] {{flagteam|USA|1996 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n |url=http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1996/1996v1.pdf \n |title=The Official Report of the Centennial Olympic Games, Volume I Planning and Organization \n |publisher=Peachtree Publishers \n |location=Atlanta \n |year=1997 \n |format=PDF \n |accessdate=19 February 2014 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616041701/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1996/1996v1.pdf \n |archivedate=16 June 2012 \n}}\n* {{cite web\n |url=http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1996/1996v2.pdf \n |title=The Official Report of the Centennial Olympic Games, Volume II The Centennial Olympic Games \n |publisher=Peachtree Publishers \n |location=Atlanta \n |year=1997 \n |format=PDF \n |accessdate=19 February 2014 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715195716/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1996/1996v2.pdf \n |archivedate=15 July 2012 \n}}\n* {{cite web\n |url=http://la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1996/1996v3.pdf \n |title=The Official Report of the Centennial Olympic Games, Volume III The Competition Results \n |publisher=Peachtree Publishers \n |location=Atlanta \n |year=1997 \n |format=PDF \n |accessdate=19 February 2014 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120716071036/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1996/1996v3.pdf \n |archivedate=16 July 2012 \n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n <ref name=\"A\">{{cite web\n |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/po/gerhard-potma-1.html \n |title=Gerhard Potma Bio, Stats, and Results \n |publisher=Sports-Reference.com \n |work=Olympic Sports \n |accessdate=2014-01-10 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213084402/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/po/gerhard-potma-1.html \n |archivedate=2013-12-13 \n}}</ref>\n <ref name=\"B\">{{cite web\n   |url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:011020009:mpeg21:a0277\n   |title      = Twentse surfster redt eer zeilvloot\n   |newspaper  = Nieuwsblad van het Noorden\n   |date       = 3 April 1992\n   |language   = Dutch\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=\"C\">{{cite web\n   |url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010646702:mpeg21:a0404\n   |title      = WAARDIG AFSCHEID VAN ZEILPLOEG\n   |newspaper  = De Telegraaf\n   |date       = 4 April 1992\n   |language   = Dutch\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=\"D\">{{cite web\n   |url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010637398:mpeg21:a0182\n   |title      = Veertien zeilers naar Barcelona\n   |newspaper  = Limburgsch dagblad\n   |date       = 1 June 1992\n   |language   = Dutch\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}</ref>\n <ref name=\"E\">{{cite web\n   |url        = http://resolver.kb.nl/resolve?urn=ddd:010646586:mpeg21:a0537\n   |title      = Zeilers aan alle kanten voorbijgevarer\n   |newspaper  = [[De Telegraaf]]\n   |date       = 30 July 1992\n   |language   = Dutch\n   |accessdate = 19 February 2014\n  }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Potma, Gerhard}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Sneek]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Friesland]]\n[[Category:Dutch male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Dutch windsurfers]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of the Netherlands]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Gerhard Potma\n| image          = Gerhard-potma.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| caption        = Gerhard Potma in May 2005\n| birth_name     =\n| fullname       = Gerhardus Johannes Cornelis Potma\n| nickname       =\n| nationality    = Dutch\n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1967|08|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Sneek]]\n| death_date     = {{Death date and age|2006|03|31|1967|08|29|df=y}}\n| death_place    =\n| height         = {{convert|1.84|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         =\n| classes        = [[Flying Dutchman (dinghy)|Flying Dutchman]]<br />[[Soling]]\n| club           =\n| collegeteam    =\n| coach          =\n| medaltemplates-title = Competition record\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCountry|{{NED}}}}\n {{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]] [[File:Olympic rings without rims.svg|50px]]}}\n  {{Medal|18th|[[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]]|[[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]]}}\n  {{Medal|15th|[[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|1996 Savannah]]|[[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|Soling]]}}\n| show-medals    = yes\n| updated        = 20 February 2014\n}}\n\n'''Gerhard Potma''' (29 August 1967, in [[Sneek]] \u2013 31 March 2006, in Sneek) was a [[sailor]] from the [[Netherlands]],<ref name=\"A\" /> who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]]. Potma as crew in the Dutch  [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Flying Dutchman|Flying Dutchman]]<ref name=\"B\" /> with his brother, [[Willem Potma]],<ref name=\"C\" /> as helmsman took the 18th place.<ref name=\"D\" /><ref name=\"E\" /> In [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|1996]] Potma returned to the Olympics in [[Savannah, Georgia|Savannah]]. Again with his brother as helmsman and [[Frank Hettinga]] as crew. Potma took 15th place in the [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|Soling]].<ref name=\"A\" />\n{{Footer Dutch Champions in Soling}}\n{{1992DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n{{1996DutchOlympicSailingTeam}}\n==Further reading==\n\n===[[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Olympics (Barcelona)]] {{flagteam|ESP|1992 Summer}}===\n* {{cite web\n